Oh, Godzilla!

977
01:18:40,660 --> 01:18:43,699
I started out with Robb
when I was 14, 15 years old

978
01:18:43,780 --> 01:18:48,619
and we said, "We're going to do it till
we're old men." We really meant that.

979
01:18:49,060 --> 01:18:53,939
We had that 15 minutes of fame
and then it's gone.

980
01:18:54,020 --> 01:18:56,259
So that's the way I kind of look at it.

981
01:18:56,340 --> 01:19:01,379
So I was lucky enough to have that moment,
and I've made, basically...

982
01:19:02,460 --> 01:19:08,979
It was enough of a moment that it prolonged
and gave me a career that's 30 years long.

983
01:19:09,060 --> 01:19:12,539
So it was a great achievement,
a fantastic achievement.

984
01:19:12,620 --> 01:19:15,219
Nothing to ever look down at
or not to be proud of

985
01:19:15,300 --> 01:19:16,739
and that's the way I really look at it.

986
01:19:16,980 --> 01:19:22,499
You don't think about it. Life flies by, man.
That's all I'm learning here, you know.

987
01:19:22,580 --> 01:19:26,579
Before you know it, life's done.
And it didn't seem that long.

988
01:19:27,220 --> 01:19:30,499
That's what Robbo was learning
about a lot of things.

989
01:19:30,580 --> 01:19:33,219
The music lasts forever.

990
01:19:34,660 --> 01:19:37,459
Maybe the debt does, too,
but the bottom line is,

991
01:19:37,540 --> 01:19:42,499
the music lasts forever and that's the art
and that's the most important thing.

992
01:19:42,580 --> 01:19:46,979
There's tons of bands that can sell
millions of records, obviously,

993
01:19:47,060 --> 01:19:49,459
but how many bands
can you think of, honestly,

994
01:19:49,540 --> 01:19:52,099
that have stayed together for 30 years?

995
01:19:52,180 --> 01:19:56,099
You've got a couple. You've got
The Rolling Stones, you've got The Who,

996
01:19:56,180 --> 01:19:57,259
and you've got Anvil.
